    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix memory allocation issue in UE initialization causing downstream configuration mismatch\n\n### Summary\nThe `init_UE` function and related stub initialization functions were allocating memory with incorrect dimensions, causing a configuration mismatch between protocol layers. This resulted in inconsistent behavior downstream of the initialization functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `executables/lte-ue.c`: Fixed memory allocation in `init_UE`, `init_UE_stub`, and `init_UE_stub_single_thread` functions to use correct dimensions without extra +1 padding.\n\n### Reproduction\nUsers may observe inconsistent behavior when running LTE UE simulations, particularly when multiple component carriers are configured. The issue manifests as downstream protocol layer mismatches that can cause unexpected behavior in RRC connection establishment or data transmission.\n\n"
}